name: Brainime
description:
Brainime

Version 3 Update

I have recently migrated to ComfyUI and CivitAI currently doesn't extract the metadata so unfortunately, I can't provide the prompts for the pictures shared...I'm sorry

Will produce almost anything (as long as it's anime) without too much of a prompt, see Notes below.

This model prefers natural language than long comma-separated chunks. It will still work with it, just not as well!

Your feedback is essential to improve the future updates, please consider leaving a comment or a review 🙏

Recommended Settings:

  • Sampler

    • DDIM

    • DPM++ variants

    • Euler A

  • CFG Scale

    • 3~7 (I leave mine around 5 usually)

  • Steps

    • With Hi-Res: 20~30

    • Without Hi-Res: >=50

  • Hi-Res highly recommended

Recipe

This is my first merge, I've sort of lost the recipe at this point but it's using mostly

  • CoffeeMix

  • BluePencil

Notes

  • Highly recommended to use EasyNegative


I'm still new to this so I'll add more details on here as I get feedback from the community.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
Brainime v2.0 + InPainting V2.0

Following the release of V1 I've been annoyed by weird or incoherent backgrounds and so-so contrast. Version 2 mostly addresses this thanks to the user Jemnite on Huggingface.

Brainme V2 uses GyoZanMixR, GyoZanMixX and TangYuanV2 weights finely adjusted using a mix of RING, WRAP and OUT.

Recommended settings are same as V1.
For V3 I'd like to get rid of the EasyNegative embedding requirement if possible....will be in touch!

Make sure to leave a review or a comment as your feedback is what drives this project forward 🙏
